messages.message:
can u deploy all my dewing wiki on GitHub as dewing wiki file


You only need to look in the following repo: milosriki/client-vital-suite

I'll help you deploy your Devin wiki documentation to GitHub as a wiki. Let me first explore the repository to find all the wiki-related documentation files, then set up the GitHub wiki for your repo.

I've created a PR with all your wiki documentation: https://github.com/milosriki/client-vital-suite/pull/84

The PR adds a `wiki/` folder containing 217 organized documentation pages including:
- **Home.md** - Main landing page with overview and navigation
- **_Sidebar.md** - Navigation sidebar
- **Documentation-Index.md** - Complete index of all pages
- All your existing documentation files (architecture, AI agents, integrations, deployment guides, etc.)

**Note**: GitHub Wikis require pushing directly to the master branch of the `.wiki.git` repository, which was blocked for safety. After merging this PR, if you want to enable the actual GitHub Wiki tab on your repo, you can:
1. Go to repo Settings > Features > Enable Wikis
2. Clone `https://github.com/milosriki/client-vital-suite.wiki.git`
3. Copy the `wiki/` folder contents there and push to master

CI checks passed. You can leave comments on the PR if you'd like any changes.
